<DIV bclHeader>


<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;tab-stops:center 3.25in right 6.5in;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face="Times New Roman,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<h2 style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:right;"><a name="EHWcf28dd4f_bf3e_4aa6_a865_43a038"></a><a name="EHWcf28dd4f_bf3e_4aa6_a865_43a038_bclEnd"></a><b><u><font face=Calibri,sans-serif style="font-size:11.0pt;">Exhibit 99.1</font></u></b></h2>

<h2 align=left style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:left;"><b><u><font face=Calibri,sans-serif style="font-size:11.0pt;">FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</font></u></b></h2>

<h3 style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;"><b><font face=Calibri,sans-serif style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></b></h3>

<h3 style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;text-align:center;"><a name="EHWf6463c9e_09bc_4a2a_8940_c77a8b"></a><b><font face=Calibri,sans-serif style="font-size:11.0pt;">BENCHMARK ELECTRONICS <a name="EHW440c6f31_4f68_45b6_ba98_fa9b1c"></a><a name="EHWf6463c9e_09bc_4a2a_8940_c77a8b_bclEnd"></a>REPORTS <a name="EHW464a8864_f9ee_47b6_b333_689f70"></a><a name="EHW104a571a_ece5_4842_a395_8ab2d1"></a><a name="EHW104a571a_ece5_4842_a395_8ab2d1_bclEnd"></a><a name="EHW440c6f31_4f68_45b6_ba98_fa9b1c_bclEnd"></a><a name="EHW464a8864_f9ee_47b6_b333_689f70_bclEnd"></a>SECOND QUARTER RESULTS</font></b></h3>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol style="border:none;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;</font></font><font style="border:none;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Revenue
of $664 million at the high end of guidance</font></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol style="border:none;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;</font></font><font style="border:none;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Non-GAAP
operating margin increased 40 basis points quarter-over-quarter</font></font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol style="border:none;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;</font></font><font style="border:none;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Strong operating cash flow of $52 million</font></font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-left:.5in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;</font><font style="border:none;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Returned $19 million to shareholders
through share repurchases</font></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><a name="EHW5cda04ce_b0db_40c1_ae1a_30af5d"></a><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">ANGLETON, TX, July <a name="EHWafaf0cee_a8a6_42d5_914d_94d91d"></a><a name="EHW5cda04ce_b0db_40c1_ae1a_30af5d_bclEnd"></a>23<a name="EHW3c4bf39b_f9b1_4542_bd54_f09e67"></a><a name="EHWafaf0cee_a8a6_42d5_914d_94d91d_bclEnd"></a>, 201<a name="EHW287cb344_aeaf_4514_8dfe_050c74"></a><a name="EHW3c4bf39b_f9b1_4542_bd54_f09e67_bclEnd"></a>5<a name="EHW7ad03acb_9aff_4292_98e0_f5353b"></a><a name="EHW287cb344_aeaf_4514_8dfe_050c74_bclEnd"></a> &#8211; Benchmark Electronics, Inc. (NYSE: BHE)<a name="EHW4d8ee4ca_4edf_494a_b384_1a84cb"></a><a name="EHW7ad03acb_9aff_4292_98e0_f5353b_bclEnd"></a> today announced<a name="EHW4b941254_0b9c_4001_810d_290883"></a><a name="EHW4d8ee4ca_4edf_494a_b384_1a84cb_bclEnd"></a> financial results for the<a name="EHW4b941254_0b9c_4001_810d_290883_bclEnd"></a> <a name="EHW27e0f169_8b4d_410f_bf5c_6ac428"></a>quarter <a name="EHW3495905c_df6b_414b_a6d2_6d8527"></a><a name="EHW27e0f169_8b4d_410f_bf5c_6ac428_bclEnd"></a>end<a name="EHW3495905c_df6b_414b_a6d2_6d8527_bclEnd"></a>ed <a name="EHW15c0a19b_1871_4969_98b2_9605eb"></a>June 30, 2015<a name="EHW685afa42_c39e_4797_8470_c8860c"></a><a name="EHW15c0a19b_1871_4969_98b2_9605eb_bclEnd"></a><a name="EHW685afa42_c39e_4797_8470_c8860c_bclEnd"></a>.</font></p>

<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face="Times New Roman,serif" style="border:none;"><font face="Times New Roman,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></font></p>

<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;"><font style="border:none;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#8220;Benchmark performed well, as evidenced by our 4.2%
non-GAAP operating margin and revenue at the high end of our previously
announced guidance range,&#8221; said Gayla Delly, Benchmark&#8217;s President and CEO.
&#8220;Despite broad variability in end-market demand, consistent execution resulted
in year-over-year revenue increases in the medical and test</font></font><font style="border:none;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;"> &amp; </font></font><font style="border:none;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">instrumentation sectors where we have had strong new
program bookings in the last 12 months. We also experienced higher demand
during the quarter from computing and telecom customers.&#8221;</font></font></p>

<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;"><font style="border:none;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#8220;Second quarter new program bookings should result in
annualized revenue of $110-130 million when fully launched within the next
12-18 months. Bookings again aligned well with our focus on early engineering
engagement and long-term manufacturing solutions for customers in both higher
growth and traditional markets.&#8221;</font></font></p>

<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;"><font style="border:none;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#8220;Benchmark returned $19 million to shareholders through
share repurchases during the second quarter, and a total of $66 million over
the last 12 months. We continue to have a strong balance sheet and the
financial flexibility to simultaneously repurchase shares, reinvest in the
business, and support strategic growth initiatives.&#8221;</font></font></p>

<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;"><font style="border:none;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Delly concluded, &#8220;We remain focused on our key strategic
priorities that drive value for our customers and shareholders, including
diversification of our portfolio towards higher margin programs, strong
execution linked to lean and operational initiatives, and working capital </font></font><!-- Do not modify beyond this point! !--><a name=bcl_connect_next></a></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;tab-stops:center 3.25in right 6.5in;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<DIV bclHeader>


<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;tab-stops:center 3.25in right 6.5in;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>


</DIV>
<p style="border:none;margin:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;"><a name=bcl_connect_prev></a><!-- Do not modify before this point! !--><font style="border:none;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">management. Our results this quarter show continued
progress in each of these long-term objectives.&#8221;</font></font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><b><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Second Quarter 2015 Financial Highlights</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Cash flows from operating activities were $52 million</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Cash and cash equivalents were $409 million at June 30, 2015</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Accounts receivable were $501 million at June 30, 2015;
calculated days sales outstanding were 68 days compared to 71 days at March 31,
2015</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Inventories were $445 million at June 30, 2015; inventory turns
were 5.5 times compared to 5.3 at March 31, 2015</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:.5in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Restructuring charges and integration costs totaled $2 million</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">The cash
conversion cycle improved by eight days from the previous quarter driven by
improvements in receivables, payables and inventory. Benchmark expects further
improvements throughout the year.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><b><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">Second Quarter 2015 Industry Sector Update</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:10.0pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">The following
table sets forth revenue by industry sector for the referenced quarters.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font face="Times New Roman,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:normal;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Revenues across all sectors improved quarter-over-quarter.
Revenues from Industrial Controls benefitted from the positive impact of new
program introductions, offsetting weaker demand for programs related to energy markets.
Telecommunications and Computing customer revenues improved with strong sales
in the final month of the quarter. Medical and Test </font><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;">&amp;&nbsp;</font><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;"> Instrumentation grew at a healthy pace with the
successful qualification of new products.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><b><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Second Quarter 2015 Bookings Update</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">New program bookings
were $110-130 million</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">13 engineering awards
supporting early engagement opportunities</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">29 manufacturing
wins across all market sectors</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;</font></p>




<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><b><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>


<DIV bclFooter>


<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;tab-stops:center 3.25in right 6.5in;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>


</DIV>
</DIV><HR noshade STYLE="page-break-after: always" align="center" width="100%" size=2><a name="page_3"></a><DIV bclPageBorder STYLE="PADDING-TOP: 0in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 100%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in">

<DIV bclHeader>


<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;tab-stops:center 3.25in right 6.5in;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>


</DIV>
<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><b><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Margin
Improvement Initiatives</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Benchmark continues to
diversify its portfolio into higher margin business sectors and pursue lean and
operational excellence initiatives. Improved operating margins reflect the
benefits of these programs and the Company expects further benefits to accrue
over time. Benchmark remains committed to achieving its long-term goal of a 4.5%
operating margin.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><b><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Capital Allocation</font></b></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Second quarter 2015 common share repurchases totaled $19 million
or 0.8 million shares</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Amount remaining on current share repurchase program is $69
million</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Over the past three years, more than 50% of free cash flows returned
to shareholders through buybacks</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">In addition to ongoing
share repurchases, Benchmark has spent $8 million in the second quarter and $25
million year-to-date on capital expenditures related to improving operations
and expanding capabilities for customers. For the full year, capital
expenditures are expected to range from $40-50 million.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><b><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Third Quarter 2015 Outlook</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Revenue
between $635-$665 million</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Diluted
earnings per share between $0.38-$0.42 (excluding restructuring charges)</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><b><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Second Quarter 2015 Results
Conference Call Details</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">A conference call hosted
by Benchmark management will be held today at 10:00 am (Central Time) to
discuss the financial results of the Company and its future outlook. This call
will be broadcast via the internet and may be accessed by logging on to the
Company&#8217;s website at www.bench.com.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><b><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">About Benchmark
Electronics, Inc.</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;layout-grid-mode:line;line-height:115%;">Benchmark provides integrated manufacturing, design and
engineering services to original equipment manufacturers of industrial control
equipment (including equipment for the aerospace and defense industries),
telecommunication equipment, computers and related products for business
enterprises, medical devices, and test and instrumentation products.
Benchmark&#8217;s global operations include facilities in seven countries, and its
common shares trade on the New York Stock Exchange under the symbol BHE.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><b><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><b><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">For More Information, Please Contact:</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;layout-grid-mode:line;line-height:normal;">Lisa K. Weeks, VP of
Strategy &amp; Investor Relations </font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;layout-grid-mode:line;line-height:normal;">979-849-6550 (ext.
1361) or lisa.weeks@bench.com</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><b><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><b><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Non-GAAP Financial Measures</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">This
press release includes financial measures for earnings and earnings per share
that exclude certain items and therefore do not follow U.S. generally accepted
accounting principles (GAAP). A detailed reconciliation between the GAAP
results and results excluding special items (non-GAAP) is included at the end
of this press release. Management discloses non-GAAP information to provide
investors with additional information to analyze the Company&#8217;s performance and
underlying trends. Management uses non-GAAP measures of net income and earnings
per share that exclude certain items in order to better assess operating
performance and help investors compare results with our previous guidance. Our
non-GAAP information is not necessarily comparable to non-GAAP information used
by other companies. Non-GAAP information should not be viewed as a substitute
for, or superior to, net income or other data prepared in accordance with GAAP
as measures of our profitability or liquidity. Users of this financial information
should consider the types of events and transactions for which adjustments have
been made.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><b><font color=black face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;page-break-after:avoid;"><b><font color=black face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">Forward-Looking Statements</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">This
press release contains certain forward-looking statements within the scope of
the Securities Act of 1933 and the Securities Exchange Act of 1934. The words
&#8220;expect,&#8221; &#8220;estimate,&#8221; &#8220;anticipate,&#8221; &#8220;predict,&#8221; &#8220;goals&#8221; and similar terms, and
the negatives thereof, often identify forward-looking statements, which are not
limited to historical facts. Our forward-looking statements include, among
other things, those relating to future revenues from new program bookings,
share repurchases, capital investment, strategic growth initiatives, cash
management, operating margins, revenues, earnings per share, and other
statements, express or implied, concerning: future operating results or the
ability to generate sales, income or cash flow; and Benchmark&#8217;s business and
growth strategies, including expected internal growth and performance goals.
Although Benchmark believes these statements are based upon reasonable
assumptions, they involve risks and uncertainties relating to our operations,
markets and business environment generally. If one or more of these risks or
uncertainties materialize, or underlying assumptions prove incorrect, actual
outcomes may vary materially from those indicated.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;">All forward-looking
statements included in this release are based upon information available to
Benchmark as of the date of this release, and the Company assumes no obligation
to update them. Readers are advised to consult further disclosures on related
subjects, particularly in Item 1A, &#8220;Risk Factors&#8221; of the Company&#8217;s Annual
Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December 31, 2014, in its other filings
with the Securities and Exchange Commission and in its press releases.</font></p>

<P STYLE="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 1px; color: White; text-align: center"> design develop deliver  advanced technology 2 Forward - Looking Statements This document contains forward - looking statements within the scope of the Securities Act of 1933 and the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 . The words &#8220;expect,&#8221; &#8220;estimate,&#8221; &#8220;anticipate,&#8221; &#8220;predict &#8221; and similar expressions, and the negatives thereof, often identify forward - looking statements, which are not limited to historical facts . Our forward - looking statements include, among other things : future revenue estimates based on new program bookings ; guidance for the third quarter of 2015 relating to sales, operating margin, tax rate, and earnings per share ; other statements, express or implied, concerning future operating results or margins, the ability to generate sales, income or cash flow, and Benchmark&#8217;s business and growth strategies, including expected internal growth and performance goals . Although Benchmark believes these statements are based upon reasonable assumptions, they involve risks and uncertainties relating to our operations, markets and business environment generally . If one or more of these risks or uncertainties materialize, or underlying assumptions prove incorrect, actual outcomes may vary materially from those indicated . All forward - looking statements included in this document are based upon information available to Benchmark as of the date of this document, and the Company assumes no obligation to update them . Readers are advised to consult further disclosures on related subjects, particularly in Item 1 A, &#8220;Risk Factors&#8221; of the Company&#8217;s Annual Report on Form 10 - K for the year ended December 31 , 2014 , in its other filings with the Securities and Exchange Commission and in its press releases . This document includes certain financial measures, such as earnings and earnings per share, that exclude certain items and therefore are not in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles (&#8220;GAAP&#8221;) . A detailed reconciliation between GAAP results and results excluding special items (&#8220;non - GAAP&#8221;) is included in our earnings release and in the Appendix of this document .</P>
